local function getSlotId(itemName)
    local inventorySize = 16
    for i = 1, inventorySize do
        turtle.select(i)
        if turtle.getItemDetail() and turtle.getItemDetail().name == itemName then
            return i
        end
    end
    error("error: out of " .. itemName)
    return -1
end

while 1 do
    local logSlot = getSlotId("minecraft:oak_log")
    if logSlot == -1 then
        exit()
    end
    turtle.select(logSlot)
    turtle.place()

    local axeSlot = getSlotId("minecraft:stone_axe")
    if axeSlot == -1 then
        exit()
    end
    turtle.select(axeSlot)
    turtle.place()

    local alloySlot = getSlotId("create:andesite_alloy")
    if alloySlot == -1 then
        exit()
    end
    turtle.select(alloySlot)
    turtle.place()

    turtle.dig()
end

FTB Turtle harvest crops field
content:
local fieldLength = 18
local fieldWidth = 9

local function harvestRow()
    -- assuming we're ON the first field, field is in front of us
    for i = 0, fieldLength do
    	turtle.placeDown()
		turtle.suckDown()
        turtle.forward()
    end
end

local function harvestField()
    -- assuming we're ON the first field, field is in front of us and to the left
    
    for i = 0, fieldWidth do
        harvestRow()
        
        if i % 2 == 0 then
            turtle.turnLeft()
            turtle.forward()
            turtle.turnLeft()
        else
            turtle.turnRight()
            turtle.forward()
            turtle.turnRight()
        end
        
    end
end

turtle.forward()
harvestField()

title: PlayerTracker
content:
local playerDetector = peripheral.find('playerDetector')
local monitor = peripheral.find('monitor')
local w,h = term.getSize()

function startMonitor()
  monitor.setCursorPos(1,1)
  monitor.setTextScale(1)
  wm, hm = monitor.getSize()
  monitor.clear()
end

function newLine()
  local _,cY= monitor.getCursorPos()
  monitor.setCursorPos(1,cY+1)
end

function main()
    startMonitor()
	local online = playerDetector.getOnlinePlayers()
		for i, player in pairs(online) do
 			local pos = playerDetector.getPlayerPos(player)
 			local x, y, z = pos.x, pos.y, pos.z
 			monitor.write(player .. ' x:' .. x .. " y: " .. y .. " z: " .. z)
 			newLine()
	end
	sleep(0.1)
	main()
end

main()

title: r_icinga
content:
#!/bin/bash

API_USER=""
API_PASS=""
API_BASE=""


usage() {
  echo "Usage: $0 -H <HOST> [-s <Service>] [-t <Time><m|h|d|w|M|y>] [-c Comment] [-a Author] -o <downtime|remove-downtime|reschedule-check|acknowledge-problem>"
}

downtime() {

 # Check that all Variables are set
 if [ -z "${MYHOST}" ]
 then
   echo "host parameter (-h or --host) is missing. Aborting."
   usage
   exit 1
 elif [ -z "${TIME}" ]
 then
   echo "time parameter (-t or --time) is missing. Aborting."
   usage
   exit 1
 fi

 if [ -z "${COMMENT}" ]
 then
   COMMENT="Planned downtime"
 fi

 if [ -z "${AUTHOR}" ]
 then
   AUTHOR="LBA Admin"
 fi

 # Prepare the JSON Object
 JSON=$(jo -p type=Host filter="host.name==\"${MYHOST}\"" all_services=true author="${AUTHOR}" comment="${COMMENT}" fixed=true start_time="$(date +%s -d "+0 hour")" end_time="$(date +%s -d "${TIME}")")

 # Use the icinga2 API
 curl -k -s -u ${API_USER}:${API_PASS} -H "Accept: application/json" -X POST ${API_BASE}actions/schedule-downtime -d "${JSON}"  | jq

}

remove-downtime() {

 # Check that all Variables are set
 if [ -z "${MYHOST}" ]
 then
   echo "host parameter (-H or --host) is missing. Aborting."
   usage
   exit 1
 fi

 if [ -z "${COMMENT}" ]
 then
   COMMENT="Removed downtime"
 fi

 if [ -z "${AUTHOR}" ]
 then
   AUTHOR="LBA Admin"
 fi

 # Prepare the JSON object
 JSON=$(jo -p type=Host filter="host.name==\"${MYHOST}\"" author="${AUTHOR}" comment="${COMMENT}")

 # Use the icinga2 API
 curl -k -s -u ${API_USER}:${API_PASS} -H 'Accept: application/json' -X POST ${API_BASE}'actions/remove-downtime' -d "${JSON}" | jq

}

reschedule-check() {
 # Check that all Variables are set
 if [ -z "${MYHOST}" ]
 then
   echo "host parameter (-H or --host) is missing. Aborting."
   usage
   exit 1
 elif [ -z "${SERVICE}" ]
 then
   echo "service paramter (-s or --service) is missing. Aborting."
   usage
   exit 1
 fi

 JSON=$(jo -p type=Service filter="service.name==\"${SERVICE}\" && host.name==\"${MYHOST}\"" force=true)

 curl -k -s -u ${API_USER}:${API_PASS} -H "Accept: application/json" -X POST ${API_BASE}'actions/reschedule-check' -d "$JSON" | jq
}



acknowledge-problem() {
 # Check that all Variables are set
 if [ -z "${MYHOST}" ]
 then
   echo "host parameter (-H or --host) is missing. Aborting."
   usage
   exit 1
 elif [ -z "${SERVICE}" ]
 then
   echo "service parameter (-s or --service) is missing. Aborting."
   usage
   exit 1
 elif [ -z "${COMMENT}" ]
 then
   echo "comment parameter (-c or --comment) is missing. Aborting."
   usage
   exit 1
 elif [ -z "${TIME}" ]
 then
   echo "time parameter (-t or --time) is missing. Aborting."
   usage
   exit 1
 fi

 if [ -z "${AUTHOR}" ]
 then
   AUTHOR="LBA Admin"
 fi

 # Prepare the JSON object
 JSON=$(jo -p type=Service filter="service.name==\"${SERVICE}\" && host.name==\"${MYHOST}\"" author="${AUTHOR}" comment="$COMMENT" notify=true expiry="$(date +%s -d "${TIME}")")

 curl -k -s -u ${API_USER}:${API_PASS} -H 'Accept: application/json' -X POST ${API_BASE}'actions/acknowledge-problem' -d "$JSON" | jq


}

##### MAIN #####

if [ $# -eq 0 ]
then
  usage
else

  while [[ $# -gt 0 ]]; do
    key="$1"
    case "$key" in
      -h | --help)
        usage
        exit 0
        ;;
      -H | --host)
        MYHOST="$2"
        shift
        shift
        ;;
      -s | --service)
        SERVICE="$2"
        shift
        shift
        ;;
      -t | --time)
        TIME="$2"
        shift
        shift
        ;;
      -c | --comment)
        COMMENT="$2"
        shift
        shift
        ;;
      -a | --author)
        AUTHOR="$2"
        shift
        shift
        ;;
      -o | --option)
        OPTION="$2"
        shift
        shift
        ;;
      *)
        usage
        exit 0
        ;;
    esac
  done


  # Translate TIME into a nice date format
  if [ ! -z "${TIME}" ]
  then
    case "${TIME:0-1}" in
      m)
        TIME="+${TIME%?} min"
        ;;
      h)
        TIME="+${TIME%?} hour"
        ;;
      d)
        TIME="+${TIME%?} day"
        ;;
      w)
        TIME="+${TIME%?} week"
        ;;
      M)
        TIME="+${TIME%?} month"
        ;;
      y)
        TIME="+${TIME%?} year"
        ;;
      *)
        echo "Sorry, ${TIME:0-1} is not supported."
        exit 1
        ;;
    esac
  fi

  case $OPTION in
     downtime)
       downtime
       ;;
     remove-downtime)
       remove-downtime
       ;;
     reschedule-check)
       reschedule-check
       ;;
     acknowledge-problem)
       acknowledge-problem
       ;;
     *)
       echo "$OPTION is unknown"
       usage
       exit 1
       ;;
  esac
fi
